#ROOM
Vnum     33000
Name     &OThe Shimmering Pass&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The blinding white salt of Thousand Needles abruptly ends here, giving
way to an endless ocean of golden sand. The heat is dry and absolute.
The desert of Tanaris stretches out before you, unforgiving and vast.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    26015
Desc      Back to the Shimmering Flats.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33001
Desc      The road to Gadgetzan.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33009 2 33000
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33001
Name     &OThe Gadgetzan Approach&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A wide, sandy trail marked by bleached animal skulls and rusted
mechanical parts. In the distance, the high metal walls of a desert
fortress rise above the shifting dunes.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33000
Desc      The Shimmering Pass.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33002
Desc      Gadgetzan North Gate.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset O 0 33015 1 33001
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33002
Name     &xGadgetzan - North Gate&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Massive steel doors stand open, heavily guarded by goblin bruisers.
Water purifiers hum loudly along the walls, providing the lifeblood
that keeps this neutral trading post alive.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33001
Desc      The desert approach.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33003
Desc      Gadgetzan Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33002 2 33002
  Reset E 1 33002 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33003
Name     &xGadgetzan - Central Square&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The heart of the goblin city. Tents and metal shacks are crammed
together, offering everything from rare engineering schematics to
questionable drinking water. An arena sits to the east.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33002
Desc      The North Gate.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33005
Desc      The South Gate.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    33004
Desc      Marin's Shop.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    33025
Desc      The Thunderdrome.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33002 3 33003
Reset O 0 33012 1 33003
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33004
Name     &xMarin Noggenfogger's Shop&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     A cramped, poorly ventilated shack filled with bubbling beakers and
vats of brightly colored liquids. It smells strongly of sulfur and
sweet desert cactus.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    33003
Desc      The Central Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33003 1 33004
  Reset G 1 33000 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33005
Name     &xGadgetzan - South Gate&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     The southern exit from the safety of the goblin city. The metal walls
are scored by sandstorms and the occasional stray bullet. Beyond
these gates lies the deep desert.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33003
Desc      The Central Square.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33006
Desc      The Deep Desert.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33002 2 33005
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33006
Name     &OThe Tanaris Desert&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     Rolling dunes of golden sand stretch out in every direction. The heat
distorts the horizon, making it incredibly difficult to navigate.
Predators stalk the shadows of the dunes.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33005
Desc      Gadgetzan South Gate.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    33008
Desc      Toward Steamwheedle Port.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33012
Desc      Waterspring Field.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33009 2 33006
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33007
Name     &OThe Noonshade Ruins&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The crumbling, sand-swept remains of an ancient troll city. Broken
pillars and cracked stone altars poke out from the dunes, guarded
by the remnants of the Sandfury tribe.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    33012
Desc      Waterspring Field.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33005 2 33007
  Reset G 1 33014 10
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33008
Name     &OThe Road to Steamwheedle&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     The sand begins to thin, replaced by hard-packed earth and the smell
of salt water. A trail leads east toward the goblin port on the
Great Sea.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    33006
Desc      The desert.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    33009
Desc      Steamwheedle Port.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33009
Name     &xSteamwheedle Port&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A small, neutral harbor built on the eastern coast. Goblin ships
dock here to avoid the pirates to the south. The sound of crashing
waves provides a welcome relief from the silent desert.
~
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    33008
Desc      The desert road.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33010
Desc      The Pirate Cove.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33008 2 33009
  Reset E 1 33006 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33010
Name     &bLost Rigger Cove&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     Hidden behind a massive rock formation, this secluded cove serves as
the primary base for the Southsea pirates. Ships are anchored just
offshore, and the beach is heavily guarded.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33009
Desc      Steamwheedle Port.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33011
Desc      The Pirate Compound.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33008 3 33010
Reset O 0 33010 1 33010
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33011
Name     &bSouthsea Pirate Compound&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A fortified camp built from the timber of wrecked ships. Plunder is
piled high, and drunken pirates sing bawdy songs around a massive
bonfire in the center of the yard.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33010
Desc      The Cove.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33008 2 33011
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33012
Name     &OWaterspring Field&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A rare collection of natural wells that provide the only fresh water
for miles. The Wastewander bandits have laid claim to this area,
forcing travelers to pay a steep price or fight.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33006
Desc      The northern desert.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    33007
Desc      Noonshade Ruins.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction west~
ToRoom    33013
Desc      Wastewander Encampment.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33014
Desc      The deep sands.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33001 2 33012
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33013
Name     &OWastewander Encampment&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     A sprawling camp of dusty tents. Stolen supplies from Gadgetzan are
hoarded here. The bandits are well-armed and view any outsider as a
threat to their water supply.
~
#EXIT
Direction east~
ToRoom    33012
Desc      Waterspring Field.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33000 3 33013
  Reset E 1 33013 10 16
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33014
Name     &OThe Zul'Farrak Approach&d~
Sector   mountain~
Desc     The dunes give way to a rocky gorge. The sand here is stained a deep,
rusty red. Giant carved faces stare down from the canyon walls, a
warning to those who would enter the troll city.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33012
Desc      Waterspring Field.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33015
Desc      The Gates of Zul'Farrak.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33004 2 33014
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33015
Name     &OThe Gates of Zul'Farrak&d~
Sector   city~
Desc     Massive stone doors block the entrance to the ancient city. Sandfury
trolls patrol the ramparts above, raining spears down on any who
approach without a massive army behind them. A narrow gap between the 
heavy stone doors allows brave adventurers to slip inside.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33014
Desc      The gorge.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction south~
ToRoom    33016
Desc      The Altar of Zul.
~
#ENDEXIT
#EXIT
Direction in~
ToRoom    33030
Desc      Slip through the heavy stone doors.
~
#ENDEXIT
Reset M 0 33005 2 33015
  Reset E 1 33003 10 6
Reset M 0 33004 2 33015
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33030
Name     &OThe Sunken Portal of Zul'Farrak&d~
Sector   inside~
Flags    indoors~
Desc     You stand in the shadowed archway just beyond the main gates. The 
sounds of tribal drums and chanting echo off the sandstone walls from 
deep within the city. A swirling, sand-colored portal blocks the path 
forward, separating the outer ruins from the heavily guarded inner 
sanctum of the Sandfury tribe.
~
#EXIT
Direction out~
ToRoom    33015
Desc      Squeeze back outside the gates.
~
#ENDEXIT
#ENDROOM

#ROOM
Vnum     33016
Name     &OThe Altar of Zul&d~
Sector   field~
Desc     A blood-stained pyramid stands just outside the city gates. The Chief
of the Sandfury tribe occasionally presides over sacrifices here,
calling to the sleeping hydra god.
~
#EXIT
Direction north~
ToRoom    33015
Desc      The Gates.
~
